id: pm-3esl28
title: "GH-645: standard-depth get/show JSON omits notes without notes_count"
description: "At the default standard depth, pm get/show --json suppresses notes but exposes no notes_count or omission metadata, so agents can falsely conclude the item has no working context."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: agent-ux,"area:cli",gh-issue,json,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-22T19:01:44.269Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-23T05:34:01.240Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-23T05:34:00.488Z"
author: codex-sdk-boundary-20260722
acceptance_criteria: "Default standard-depth get/show JSON reports notes_count whenever notes are omitted; full/deep projections remain backward compatible and include notes; CLI aliases, SDK result contracts, MCP projections, TOON/JSON docs, and contract fixtures remain coherent; regression tests cover zero, one, and multiple notes plus explicit depth modes"
parent: pm-mpbb
reporter: GitHub GH-645
severity: medium
resolution: "Standard and brief get projections now expose item.notes_count whenever note bodies are omitted; deep/full reads retain note bodies without a redundant count, and narrow fields accept notes_count."
expected_result: Agents can distinguish zero notes from omitted note context without requesting a full item payload.
actual_result: "CLI, PmClient, aliases, field projection, SDK docs, focused tests, full coverage, and packed installed-consumer acceptance all confirm the truthful count contract."
affected_version: 2026.7.22
